---
title: California-Style Turkey Burgers with Avocado and Sweet Potato Fries
description: It’s no secret that we're obsessed with avocados in the HelloFresh kitchen. It’s the perfect all-purpose creamy topping! We especially love it sliced and sandwiched between this fresh Cali inspired turkey burger.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/burgers-de-dinde-a-la-californienne-a883ed14.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.ca/recipecards/card/california-style-turkey-burgers-with-avocado-5cb79f17e3f3390fc55112a2-48a4290c.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.ca/recipes/california-style-turkey-burgers-with-avocado-5cb79f17e3f3390fc55112a2
course: main course
cuisine: American
---

250 g Ground Turkey
340 g Sweet Potato, fries
2 unit Burger Bun
1 unit Avocado
170 g Beefsteak Tomato
56 g Baby Spinach
1 unit Lemon
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
6 g Garlic
3 tbsp Sour Cream
1 tbsp Dijon Mustard
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 tbsp Southwest Spice Blend
1.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt and Pepper*
¼ tsp Salt*

Preheat the oven to 450°F (to bake sweet potato fries). Start prepping when the oven comes up to temperature! Wash and dry all produce.* On a baking sheet, toss sweet potatoes with 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl). Season with salt and pepper. Bake in middle of oven, turning sweet potatoes over halfway through cooking, until golden-brown, 22-24 min.

Meanwhile, peel, then mince or grate garlic. Zest, then juice lemon(s). Cut tomato into 1/4-inch slices. Peel, pit and thinly slice avocado(s). In a small bowl combine mayo, sour cream, lemon zest, 1 tbsp lemon juice (dbl for 4 ppl). Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Set aside.

In a medium bowl, combine turkey, panko, garlic, mustard, 1 tbsp Southwest Spice Blend (dbl for 4 ppl), 1/4 tsp salt (dbl for 4 ppl). Season with pepper. Form turkey mixture into two 4-inch wide burger patties (four patties for 4 ppl). (NOTE: Your mixture may look wet, this is normal! )

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then patties. Pan-fry, until patties are golden-brown and cooked through, 5-6 min per side. (TIP: Cook to a min. internal temp. of 74°C/165°F.**)

Meanwhile, halve buns, then arrange them cut-side up on another baking sheet. Toast in top of oven, until golden-brown, 4-5 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)

Spread half the lemon aioli on buns, then layer with patties, spinach, tomato slices and avocado slices. Divide burgers and sweet potato fries between plates. Serve with remaining lemon aioli, for dipping.